  "about": {
    "heroEyebrow": "Trashium के बारे में",
    "heroTitle": "रोज़मर्रा के कचरे को बदलें",
    "heroHighlight": "कुछ मूल्यवान में",
    "heroSubtitle": "Trashium is an AI-assisted waste management platform that pays households fairly for dry recyclables, picks them up at the door, and rewards the habit of sorting — so material that used to be thrown away gets a second life.",
    "whatTitle": "Trashium क्या है",
    "whatBody": "At its simplest, Trashium is a way to schedule a doorstep pickup of dry recyclables — plastic, paper, cardboard, metals, e-waste — and get paid a fair, transparent rate for them. Underneath that, it is a small circular-economy engine: pricing driven by a machine-learning model, routing handled through neighbourhood micro-hubs, and a gamified rewards layer that keeps households sorting their waste week after week. We treat recycling less like a chore and more like a habit worth building.",
    "problemEyebrow": "जिस समस्या को हल करने निकले",
    "problemTitle": "रीसाइकिलयोग्य सामग्री कीमती है। फिर भी कोई इसे एकत्र नहीं करता।",
    "problem1": "Households throw away dry recyclables because selling small amounts to a kabadiwala isn't worth the hassle.",
    "problem2": "Scrap rates are opaque — most people have no idea what their plastic, paper or metal is actually worth.",
    "problem3": "The informal collection network is hard to reach, inconsistent, and rarely shows up on time.",
    "problem4": "Recyclable material that could re-enter the economy ends up in landfills and drains instead.",
    "missionTitle": "हमारा मिशन",
    "missionBody": "Make recycling the easy, rewarding choice for ordinary households — by paying fairly, showing up reliably, and being honest about what every kilogram is worth.",
    "visionTitle": "हमारा दृष्टिकोण",
    "visionBody": "A West Bengal where dry waste rarely reaches a landfill because a dependable, transparent network makes it easier to recycle than to throw away — and the people who do the collecting earn a steady living from it.",
    "howEyebrow": "प्लेटफ़ॉर्म कैसे काम करता है",
    "howTitle": "आपके दरवाज़े से रीसाइकलर तक, तीन कदम में",
    "step1Title": "घर से पिकअप बुक करें",
    "step1Body": "Pick your material and a slot. A verified crew comes to your door — no haggling, no carrying sacks to a scrap shop.",
    "step2Title": "पारदर्शी दर पाएं",
    "step2Body": "Rates come from a pricing model trained on two years of regional scrap data, not a number made up on the spot. Weight is verified at pickup.",
    "step3Title": "हरित क्रेडिट कमाएं",
    "step3Body": "Every kilogram you divert builds Green Credits and moves you up the eco-levels. Credits redeem for rewards and upcycled goods.",
    "circularEyebrow": "चक्रीय अर्थव्यवस्था दृष्टिकोण",
    "circularTitle": "कचरा तभी कचरा है जब चक्र टूटा हो",
    "circularBody": "A bottle thrown in a bin is rubbish. The same bottle, clean and sorted, is raw material. Trashium is built to keep that loop closed — collecting at the source, aggregating through micro-hubs, and passing clean streams to certified recyclers so the material re-enters the economy.",
    "impact1Title": "चक्र को पूरा करना",
    "impact1Body": "Clean, sorted material flows to certified recyclers — so a discarded bottle or carton becomes raw input again instead of waste.",
    "impact2Title": "संग्रहकर्ताओं के साथ काम",
    "impact2Body": "Rather than competing with the informal sector, Trashium gives collectors steady, mapped routes and predictable volumes through micro-hubs.",
    "impact3Title": "इस क्षेत्र के लिए बना",
    "impact3Body": "Operations are designed around real West Bengal towns — Rishra, Howrah, Shyamnagar, Tarakeswar and Hugli-Chinsura — not a generic metro.",
    "surveyEyebrow": "विचार कहाँ से आया",
    "surveyTitle": "हुगली क्षेत्र में एक फ़ील्ड सर्वे",
    "surveyBody1": "Trashium didn't start as an app — it started as fieldwork. We spoke with households and local scrap collectors across Rishra, Belur, Bally and Shyamnagar to understand how dry waste actually moves through these neighbourhoods. The same things came up again and again: people didn't know what their scrap was worth, pickups were unreliable, and small quantities simply weren't worth anyone's time.",
    "surveyBody2": "Those conversations shaped everything — the transparent pricing, the micro-hub routing, and the choice to launch in real towns like Rishra, Howrah, Shyamnagar, Tarakeswar and Hugli-Chinsura rather than a hypothetical city.",
    "academicTitle": "वास्तविक जड़ों वाला एक शैक्षणिक प्रोजेक्ट",
    "academicBody": "Trashium is a final-year B.Tech capstone — built by students who wanted their project to address something they could see in their own neighbourhoods. The platform brings together full-stack engineering, a machine-learning pricing pipeline, geospatial route planning, and primary field research. It is a working demonstration rather than a registered commercial service, and we're open about that throughout the site.",
    "ctaTitle": "इसे काम करते देखने के लिए तैयार हैं?",
